CREATE TABLE regions (id UInt32, name String, population UInt32);
INSERT INTO regions VALUES (1, 'Region A', 1000), (2, 'Region B', 2000), (3, 'Region C', 0);
SELECT regionToPopulation(id) AS population FROM regions WHERE id = 1;
SELECT regionToPopulation(id) AS population FROM regions WHERE id = 2;
SELECT regionToPopulation(id) AS population FROM regions WHERE id = 3;
SELECT regionToPopulation(99999) AS population;
-- Assuming 99999 is an invalid Region ID, should return 0.;
SELECT regionToPopulation(CAST(2 AS UInt32)) AS population FROM regions;
SELECT regionToPopulation(NULL) AS population;
-- Should handle NULL input gracefully.;
SELECT r.name, regionToPopulation(r.id) AS population FROM regions r WHERE regionToPopulation(r.id) > 0;
SELECT r1.name AS parent_region, r2.name AS child_region, regionToPopulation(r1.id) AS parent_population, regionToPopulation(r2.id) AS child_population FROM regions r1 JOIN regions r2 ON r1.id <> r2.id;
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM regions WHERE regionToPopulation(id) = 0;
WITH (SELECT AVG(population) FROM regions) AS avg_population SELECT name, regionToPopulation(id) / avg_population AS population_ratio FROM regions;
SELECT SUM(regionToPopulation(id)) FROM regions GROUP BY name HAVING SUM(regionToPopulation(id)) > 500;